  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nOften when you type a message and have quick enough fingers, - the message 'Send' button could be tapped really fast. Especially on low-level devices it's easy to tap Send button while the text you type is still in process of being rendered in the message input. In that case no message is sent which feels as not the best UX.\r\nCould not reproduce on iOS, but might because iPhoneX too fast enough\r\n\r\nIt's visible that Send button is pressed but no message is sent. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAny time the 'Send' message button is active, - once it tapped it - message is sent.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n![1wd1wd1wd1wd](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/93888794-21a4fc80-fcf1-11ea-9d88-232e5905cba0.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Join any chat\r\n- Start typing  a message and tap 'Send' message with a delay of 0.2-0.3sec between last char and 'Send' message being tapped \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: develop 1.7, release 1.6.1\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n",
